						<summary>

						<p>On a stone lying before the Bhadrakāḷi temple at Āraṅgipēṭa.</p>						

						<p>Eastern Gaṅga: Dēvēndravarmadēva, 7th year.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1005 <hi rend="italic">(śara-sūrya-raśmi),</hi> Dhanus, Uttarāyaṇa.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of 50 sheep made by Pedda-Allu Gōkanāyaka, a resident of Gāra-grāma for burning a perpetual lamp to the god Nārāyaṇadēva of Gāra.</p>						

						</summary>
